A marriage therapist suggests that important “conditio sine qua non” that women consider are their parents, family, children, career, studies or their mutual success – the list is endless!

Research suggests that when a woman marries an already married (with children) man, she faces psychosocial alienation. None the less, she continues to give her best to her happy family.

Delay in separation

Delaying a divorce is an emotional deadlock. Many of the divorcees, who seek legal counselling, reveal the trauma of drama before being legally separated or divorced.

Occurs mostly when the spouses are emotionally not prepared to endorse the divorce, hoping for a reversal of their marriage.

Sometimes, a non bailable offence is lodged without giving any opportunity to the innocent of his/herself. As a result, the court will not hear/execute the case.

The pending case in the law courts may add further emotional trauma and poses impending legal problems for divorcees.

Worst of all,

The long arm of emotional blackmail and abuse of Section 498A of Indian Penal Code, severely affected men as much as women.

Exceptions of failed marriages that led to a few successful post-marital relationships are rare but possible.

Women in particular,

Women seem especially vulnerable to trauma when it comes to divorce That being said, there is nothing wrong with falling in and out of love more than once in a lifetime.
